cinema.XML

Class CreateUserBookingsXML

  • Object
    • CreateXML
      • CreateUserBookingsXML

  • public class CreateUserBookingsXML
extends CreateXML
    This class extends cinema.shared_view.CreateXML. It has instance variables that define all the information about a customer booking. It defines getters and setters for these private variables. It defines a function to write the film information to an XML file using the filename and root passed in the constructor.
    Author:
    carolinesmith, daianabassi
    See Also:
    cinema.shared_view.CreateXML.

      • CreateUserBooking

        public void CreateUserBooking()
        Creates a new booking element and sets the user booking instance variables as the child elements of the booking element. Defines the booking attribute using the ID of the logged in user. Adds the new booking element to the document root and sets the root to the document. Writes the XML to the file specified in the constructor.

      • CreateInitUserBooking

        public void CreateInitUserBooking(String initID,
                                  String initFilmName,
                                  String initDate,
                                  String initTime,
                                  String initSeat)
        Creates initial user booking elements in userBookings.xml when the program is first run. It is called from cinema.CinemaMain to provide the default customer with some past bookings to see on their account page.
        Parameters:
        initID - String ID to match the ID of the default customer
        initFilmName - String film name booked
        initDate - String date booked
        initTime - String time booked
        initSeat - String seat booked
